  "notes": [
    "<strong>How to read mode-multiplexed keys:</strong> keypad rows 1&ndash;3 show four lines per key, one per mode. The colored letter (T / E / M / C) is the active slide-switch position. Slide to that position, then press the key.",
    "<strong>Slide switch is always-on:</strong> exactly one of Joy_27&ndash;30 is held at any moment. Sliding between positions briefly releases one and engages the next &mdash; no mode-multiplexed action has a plain (no-modifier) binding, so a slide-gap is harmless.",
    "<strong>Common bindings (active in all modes):</strong> all stick axes, both stick presses, top row, push buttons, POV hat (cardinals + diagonals), and keypad bottom row.",
    "<strong>POV hat diagonals = direct cockpit panel focus:</strong> &#8598; Chat, &#8599; Systems, &#8601; Nav, &#8600; Contacts. Mnemonic: &#8598;/&#8601; = left-side panels (Chat top-left, Nav left); &#8599;/&#8600; = right-side panels (Systems top-right, Contacts bottom-right).",
    "<strong>HeadLookToggle:</strong> Key 7 in Travel mode (modal) and Left Push (Joy_1) always-on. Off Joy_32 (hat press) &mdash; that button was firing HeadLook on every UI Select at stations. UIFocus is unbound on stick (POV diagonals direct-focus panels, making it redundant).",
    "<strong>Bottom-row power management:</strong> <code>* 0 # D</code> = WEP / SYS / ENG / Reset 2-2-2 (combat priority order left-to-right, reset on the right corner).",
    "<strong>Throttle vs. translation:</strong> left-stick Y is <code>AheadThrust</code> &mdash; direct fore/aft maneuvering thrust, spring-centered to zero thrust (not zero speed). Speed is set by the 0% / 50% / 100% buttons; the Y axis gives a delta on top of that. Both coexist. Left twist is <code>VerticalThrustRaw</code> (heave). Axes match VKB joystick layout: stick Y = surge, twist = heave.",
    "<strong>Pitch axis</strong> is inverted (pull back = nose up).",
    "<strong>Diagonal hat encoding:</strong> ED uses a two-key combo internally (primary cardinal + Modifier child element pointing to the second cardinal). Not a single <code>Joy_POV1UpLeft</code> key &mdash; that identifier does not exist in ED&rsquo;s binding schema."
  ]
}
